  • Method Details

    • read

      <T> SerializableObject<T> read​(InputStream input, StringPath path, Class<T> type, ObjectMetadata... metadata)
      Reads an object of the given type from the given InputStream. If no type is supplied, the type can be read from the stream by supplying ObjectMetadata.TYPE. It is required to supply a type or ObjectMetadata.TYPE.
      Parameters:
      input - The input stream
      path - Path associated with the input stream, for diagnostic purposes
      type - The type to read (if ObjectMetadata.TYPE is nor supplied
      metadata - The metadata to read
      Returns:
      The deserialized object

    • read

      default <T> SerializableObject<T> read​(InputStream input, StringPath path, ObjectMetadata... metadata)
      Reads an object from the given InputStream. The type to be read must be in the input, and metadata must specify ObjectMetadata.TYPE.
      Parameters:
      input - The input stream
      path - The path for the input stream, for diagnostic purposes
      metadata - The metadata to read from the input
